cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with machine learning tools and numerical methods for differentiable games, which are topics typically covered in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses convergence proofs and iteration complexity, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of a lower bound analysis and the extension of the p-SCLI framework suggest a focus on numerical analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper proposes a definition of the condition number, which is a concept commonly used in optimization and numerical analysis, and is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
